As you go to places like bars and restaurants, they’ll show up here. The more places you go, the more people you’ll see!
"Please let us know the reason you are turning off Places."
We won’t show where you are right now.

Places brings people together by highlighting your common interests — the bar you love, your favorite coffee shop, or the bike trail you visit on weekends. We will use your location to find the places you’ve been to recently and show you people who have been to the same spots. For example, after you’ve left a wine bar, you’ll have the chance to swipe on people who share the same (exquisite) taste. They’ll see you’ve been there too, and if you match, you can strike up a conversation knowing you already have one thing in common!

Definitely not! Users can only see where you’ve been, not where you’re at. Your current location won’t be shown to others. We’ll wait a while after you’ve left before showing you were there to potential matches. You’ll also be able to control which of your places can be seen by others by simply changing or removing it from the menu option on the place card.

Nope! This feature is used for the purpose of social places and let’s be honest, a doctor’s office is not a social call. Places like the dentist, banks, where you work, or where you live won’t be shown to other users. And if you happen to live near a social place and don’t want to be shown there, simply delete it.

There are two ways to delete a place: The first is by tapping the 3-dot menu icon on the place card and selecting Delete Place. Next, choose between the two options of Just This Once or Never Show Me Here. The second option is to go to the Settings icon on the map, tap Edit, and remove multiple places at once. Once you opt to never be shown at a Place, the decision is permanent and can’t be undone.

We are constantly improving our technology, but sometimes we can get it wrong. You may see a place show up that you didn’t actually go to, but perhaps you went somewhere nearby. You can correct this by going to the 3-dot menu option on the place card and selecting Incorrect Place. We’ll give you a list of places nearby that you may have gone to instead.

We use your location to verify that you have been to a place, but your current location will not be shown. Once you’ve left a place, it’ll take some time before showing up as one of your places, and for people to see you’ve been there. To keep this list up-to-date, your phone’s location will be updated continuously, even when you aren’t using the app. Your recent places will expire after 28 days, at which point other people won’t be able to see that you were there. Tinder will use the history of all of the places you’ve been to show you better matches and continuously improve the feature. See How do we use Places information? for more details.

It’s simple! You can turn Places on and off at any time. Just go to Settings directly from the Places screen and slide the Show me in Places toggle to the right. You will receive a confirmation prompt, followed by a confirmation screen that says Places is OFF. We might ask you for feedback on why you turned it off, so we can improve the feature in the future. Note that turning off Places does not change the location permission for Tinder on your device’s operating system. In order to manage your Tinder location settings, go to Settings on your device.

"We will use your information for the Places feature, and also to: Improve Places – We may use your information to improve the types of places we show in the feature. For example, if there aren’t many matches made at movie theaters, or many people delete movie theaters, we may remove the movies category. Develop new services - We might use this information to find you better matches. For example, if you frequent dog parks, we may use that information to recommend other dog lovers to you in a new, interest-based feature. Visit our Privacy Policy to learn more about our privacy practices."
